The paper deals with the complexity of solving parity games with costs, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of algorithms and data structures to solve these games, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of memory in solving these games, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves the use of strategies and winning conditions, which are topics in logic and verification (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
